com.orc.client
Class EchoClient

java.lang.Object
  com.orc.io.MultiplexAdapter
      com.orc.client.EchoClient
All Implemented Interfaces:
MultiplexListener
public class EchoClient
extends MultiplexAdapter

This client is designed to communicate with an EchoServer It will open the specified file and send each line as an EchoMessage The client will write data whenever the server's channel is writeable and read data whenever the server responds. In this program throughput is regarded as more important than latency so messages are queued as they are created off the file rather than sending each message as it is created.

See Also:
EchoMessage, EchoServer
